# Project File Management Best Practices
**Source:** .github/instructions/projects.instructions.md
**Last synced:** 2025-08-08

## Do this
- Keep project files minimal; rely on `Directory.Build.props` & `Directory.Packages.props` for shared settings and versions.
- Omit all package version attributes; central management handles them.
- Include only project-specific properties (OutputType, GeneratePackageOnBuild, PackageId, Description, tags, DefineConstants, non-standard configurations).
- Add only necessary PackageReference and ProjectReference entries (no versions).
- Rely on automatic test project config for *Tests projects (no explicit test packages or props).

## Avoid this
- Duplicating props (TargetFramework, Nullable, LangVersion, TreatWarningsAsErrors, analyzers) already set globally.
- Embedding package versions.
- Manually adding test dependencies in test projects.
- Overriding automatic assembly name / root namespace.

## Checklist
- [ ] No version numbers in PackageReference
- [ ] Only project-specific properties included
- [ ] Test projects omit test framework packages
- [ ] No duplicated global properties
- [ ] AssemblyName/RootNamespace not overridden

## Central Management
All versions & analyzer packages resolved via central props files; update those instead of per-project edits.
